{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MhCqrj6aGRh14Fe9kWjXZm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     2→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→\n     6→  <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n     7→  <artifactId>roster</artifactId>\n     8→  <version>1.0.0</version>\n     9→  <packaging>pom</packaging>\n    10→  <name>roster</name>\n    11→\n    12→  <properties>\n    13→    <maven.compiler.release>17</maven.compiler.release>\n    14→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    15→    <liberty.version>24.0.0.12</liberty.version>\n    16→  </properties>\n    17→\n    18→  <dependencyManagement>\n    19→    <dependencies>\n    20→      <dependency>\n    21→        <groupId>io.openliberty.features</groupId>\n    22→        <artifactId>features-bom</artifactId>\n    23→        <version>${liberty.version}</version>\n    24→        <type>pom</type>\n    25→        <scope>import</scope>\n    26→      </dependency>\n    27→    </dependencies>\n    28→  </dependencyManagement>\n    29→\n    30→  <modules>\n    31→    <module>roster-common</module>\n    32→    <module>roster-ejb</module>\n    33→    <module>roster-appclient</module>\n    34→    <module>roster-web</module>\n    35→    <module>roster-ear</module>\n    36→  </modules>\n    37→\n    38→  <build>\n    39→    <pluginManagement>\n    40→      <plugins>\n    41→        <plugin>\n    42→          <groupId>io.openliberty.tools</groupId>\n    43→          <artifactId>liberty-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    44→          <version>3.11.1</version>\n    45→        </plugin>\n    46→      </plugins>\n    47→    </pluginManagement>\n    48→  </build>\n    49→</project>\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"8303b1d3-82ec-4bb8-b8e9-c1664d6748dd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012DpBa5Z8iFP4Ac3gvwL75y","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full \\\n     6→    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     7→\n     8→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     9→\n    10→# create venv and install\n    11→RUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    12→    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python pytest\n    13→\n    14→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    15→\n    16→# Set working directory\n    17→WORKDIR /app\n    18→\n    19→# Copy all the assets\n    20→COPY . .\n    21→\n    22→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    23→\n    24→RUN mvn clean install -pl roster-ear -am\n    25→\n    26→CMD [\"mvn\", \"liberty:run\", \"-pl\", \"roster-ear\"]\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"45cd18ce-50dc-469b-b1ca-86e030721306"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HDD1MksKBFMz3oNJL6pDfB","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.roster.request;\n    13→\n    14→import java.io.Serializable;\n    15→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    16→import java.util.Collection;\n    17→import java.util.Iterator;\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→import java.util.logging.Level;\n    20→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n    21→\n    22→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    23→import jakarta.ejb.EJBException;\n    24→import jakarta.ejb.LocalBean;\n    25→import jakarta.ejb.Stateful;\n    26→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    27→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    28→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    29→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaBuilder;\n    30→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.CriteriaQuery;\n    31→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Join;\n    32→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Predicate;\n    33→import jakarta.persistence.criteria.Root;\n    34→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.IncorrectSportException;\n    35→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    36→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    37→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    38→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.League;\n    39→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.League_;\n    40→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Player;\n    41→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Player_;\n    42→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.SummerLeague;\n    43→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Team;\n    44→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.Team_;\n    45→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.WinterLeague;\n    46→\n    47→/**\n    48→ * This is the bean class for the RequestBean enterprise bean.\n    49→ *\n    50→ * @author ian\n    51→ */\n    52→@Stateful\n    53→@LocalBean\n    54→public class RequestBean implements Request, Serializable {\n    55→\n    56→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(\"roster.request.RequestBean\");\n    57→    @PersistenceContext\n    58→    private EntityManager em;\n    59→    private CriteriaBuilder cb;\n    60→\n    61→    @PostConstruct\n    62→    private void init() {\n    63→        cb = em.getCriteriaBuilder();\n    64→    }\n    65→\n    66→    @Override\n    67→    public void createPlayer(String id,\n    68→            String name,\n    69→            String position,\n    70→            double salary) {\n    71→        logger.info(\"createPlayer\");\n    72→        try {\n    73→            Player player = new Player(id, name, position, salary);\n    74→            em.persist(player);\n    75→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    76→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n    77→        }\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    @Override\n    81→    public void addPlayer(String playerId, String teamId) {\n    82→        logger.info(\"addPlayer\");\n    83→        try {\n    84→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n    85→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n    86→\n    87→            team.addPlayer(player);\n    88→            player.addTeam(team);\n    89→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    90→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n    91→        }\n    92→    }\n    93→\n    94→    @Override\n    95→    public void removePlayer(String playerId) {\n    96→        logger.info(\"removePlayer\");\n    97→        try {\n    98→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n    99→\n   100→            Collection<Team> teams = player.getTeams();\n   101→            Iterator<Team> i = teams.iterator();\n   102→            while (i.hasNext()) {\n   103→                Team team = i.next();\n   104→                team.dropPlayer(player);\n   105→            }\n   106→\n   107→            em.remove(player);\n   108→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   109→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   110→        }\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    @Override\n   114→    public void dropPlayer(String playerId, String teamId) {\n   115→        logger.info(\"dropPlayer\");\n   116→        try {\n   117→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n   118→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   119→\n   120→            team.dropPlayer(player);\n   121→            player.dropTeam(team);\n   122→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   123→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   124→        }\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    @Override\n   128→    public PlayerDetails getPlayer(String playerId) {\n   129→        logger.info(\"getPlayerDetails\");\n   130→        try {\n   131→            Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n   132→            PlayerDetails playerDetails = new PlayerDetails(player.getId(),\n   133→                    player.getName(),\n   134→                    player.getPosition(),\n   135→                    player.getSalary());\n   136→            return playerDetails;\n   137→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   138→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   139→        }\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    @Override\n   143→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersOfTeam(String teamId) {\n   144→        logger.info(\"getPlayersOfTeam\");\n   145→        List<PlayerDetails> playerList = null;\n   146→        try {\n   147→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   148→            playerList = this.copyPlayersToDetails((List<Player>) team.getPlayers());\n   149→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   150→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   151→        }\n   152→        return playerList;\n   153→    }\n   154→\n   155→    @Override\n   156→    public List<LeagueDetails> getAllLeagues() {\n   157→        logger.info(\"getAllLeagues\");\n   158→        try {\n   159→            CriteriaQuery<League> cq = cb.createQuery(League.class);\n   160→            Root<League> league = cq.from(League.class);\n   161→            cq.select(league);\n   162→            cq.orderBy(cb.asc(league.get(League_.id)));\n   163→            List<League> leagues = em.createQuery(cq).getResultList();\n   164→\n   165→            List<LeagueDetails> details = new ArrayList<>();\n   166→            for (League l : leagues) {\n   167→                details.add(new LeagueDetails(l.getId(), l.getName(), l.getSport()));\n   168→            }\n   169→            return details;\n   170→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   171→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   172→        }\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    @Override\n   176→    public List<TeamDetails> getTeamsOfLeague(String leagueId) {\n   177→        logger.info(\"getTeamsOfLeague\");\n   178→        List<TeamDetails> detailsList = new ArrayList<>();\n   179→        Collection<Team> teams = null;\n   180→\n   181→        try {\n   182→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   183→            teams = league.getTeams();\n   184→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   185→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   186→        }\n   187→\n   188→        Iterator<Team> i = teams.iterator();\n   189→        while (i.hasNext()) {\n   190→            Team team = (Team) i.next();\n   191→            TeamDetails teamDetails = new TeamDetails(team.getId(),\n   192→                    team.getName(),\n   193→                    team.getCity());\n   194→            detailsList.add(teamDetails);\n   195→        }\n   196→        return detailsList;\n   197→    }\n   198→\n   199→    @Override\n   200→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPosition(String position) {\n   201→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByPosition\");\n   202→        List<Player> players = null;\n   203→\n   204→        try {\n   205→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   206→            if (cq != null) {\n   207→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   208→\n   209→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   210→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   211→\n   212→                // set the where clause\n   213→                cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.position), position));\n   214→                cq.select(player);\n   215→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   216→                players = q.getResultList();\n   217→            }\n   218→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   219→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   220→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   221→        }\n   222→    }\n   223→\n   224→    @Override\n   225→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByHigherSalary(String name) {\n   226→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByHigherSalary\");\n   227→        List<Player> players = null;\n   228→\n   229→        try {\n   230→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   231→            if (cq != null) {\n   232→                Root<Player> player1 = cq.from(Player.class);\n   233→                Root<Player> player2 = cq.from(Player.class);\n   234→\n   235→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   236→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player1.getModel();\n   237→\n   238→                // create a Predicate object that finds players with a salary\n   239→                // greater than player1\n   240→                Predicate gtPredicate = cb.greaterThan(\n   241→                        player1.get(Player_.salary),\n   242→                        player2.get(Player_.salary));\n   243→                // create a Predicate object that finds the player based on\n   244→                // the name parameter\n   245→                Predicate equalPredicate = cb.equal(\n   246→                        player2.get(Player_.name),\n   247→                        name);\n   248→                // set the where clause with the predicates\n   249→                cq.where(gtPredicate, equalPredicate);\n   250→                // set the select clause, and return only unique entries\n   251→                cq.select(player1).distinct(true);\n   252→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   253→                players = q.getResultList();\n   254→            }\n   255→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   256→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   257→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   258→        }\n   259→    }\n   260→\n   261→    @Override\n   262→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySalaryRange(double low, double high) {\n   263→        logger.info(\"getPlayersBySalaryRange\");\n   264→        List<Player> players = null;\n   265→\n   266→        try {\n   267→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   268→            if (cq != null) {\n   269→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   270→\n   271→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   272→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   273→\n   274→                // set the where clause\n   275→                cq.where(cb.between(player.get(\n   276→                        Player_.salary),\n   277→                        low,\n   278→                        high));\n   279→                // set the select clause\n   280→                cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   281→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   282→                players = q.getResultList();\n   283→            }\n   284→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   285→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   286→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   287→        }\n   288→    }\n   289→\n   290→    @Override\n   291→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByLeagueId(String leagueId) {\n   292→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByLeagueId\");\n   293→        List<Player> players = null;\n   294→\n   295→        try {\n   296→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   297→            if (cq != null) {\n   298→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   299→                Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   300→                Join<Team, League> league = team.join(Team_.league);\n   301→\n   302→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   303→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   304→\n   305→                // set the where clause\n   306→                cq.where(cb.equal(league.get(League_.id), leagueId));\n   307→                cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   308→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   309→                players = q.getResultList();\n   310→            }\n   311→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   312→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   313→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   314→        }\n   315→    }\n   316→\n   317→    @Override\n   318→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySport(String sport) {\n   319→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByLeagueId\");\n   320→        List<Player> players = null;\n   321→\n   322→        try {\n   323→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   324→            if (cq != null) {\n   325→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   326→                Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   327→                Join<Team, League> league = team.join(Team_.league);\n   328→\n   329→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   330→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   331→\n   332→                // set the where clause\n   333→                cq.where(cb.equal(league.get(League_.sport), sport));\n   334→                cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   335→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   336→                players = q.getResultList();\n   337→            }\n   338→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   339→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   340→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   341→        }\n   342→    }\n   343→\n   344→    @Override\n   345→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByCity(String city) {\n   346→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByCity\");\n   347→        List<Player> players = null;\n   348→\n   349→        try {\n   350→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   351→            if (cq != null) {\n   352→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   353→                Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   354→\n   355→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   356→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   357→\n   358→                // set the where clause\n   359→                cq.where(cb.equal(team.get(Team_.city), city));\n   360→                cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   361→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   362→                players = q.getResultList();\n   363→            }\n   364→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   365→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   366→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   367→        }\n   368→    }\n   369→\n   370→    @Override\n   371→    public List<PlayerDetails> getAllPlayers() {\n   372→        logger.info(\"getAllPlayers\");\n   373→        List<Player> players = null;\n   374→\n   375→        try {\n   376→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   377→            if (cq != null) {\n   378→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   379→\n   380→                cq.select(player);\n   381→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   382→                players = q.getResultList();\n   383→            }\n   384→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   385→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   386→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   387→        }\n   388→    }\n   389→\n   390→    @Override\n   391→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersNotOnTeam() {\n   392→        logger.info(\"getPlayersNotOnTeam\");\n   393→        List<Player> players = null;\n   394→\n   395→        try {\n   396→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   397→            if (cq != null) {\n   398→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   399→\n   400→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   401→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   402→\n   403→                // set the where clause\n   404→                cq.where(cb.isEmpty(player.get(Player_.teams)));\n   405→                cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   406→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   407→                players = q.getResultList();\n   408→            }\n   409→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   410→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   411→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   412→        }\n   413→    }\n   414→\n   415→    @Override\n   416→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPositionAndName(String position, String name) {\n   417→        logger.info(\"getPlayersByPositionAndName\");\n   418→        List<Player> players = null;\n   419→\n   420→        try {\n   421→            CriteriaQuery<Player> cq = cb.createQuery(Player.class);\n   422→            if (cq != null) {\n   423→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   424→\n   425→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   426→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   427→\n   428→                // set the where clause\n   429→                cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.position), position),\n   430→                        cb.equal(player.get(Player_.name), name));\n   431→                cq.select(player).distinct(true);\n   432→                TypedQuery<Player> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   433→                players = q.getResultList();\n   434→            }\n   435→            return copyPlayersToDetails(players);\n   436→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   437→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   438→        }\n   439→    }\n   440→\n   441→    @Override\n   442→    public List<LeagueDetails> getLeaguesOfPlayer(String playerId) {\n   443→        logger.info(\"getLeaguesOfPlayer\");\n   444→        List<LeagueDetails> detailsList = new ArrayList<>();\n   445→        List<League> leagues = null;\n   446→\n   447→        try {\n   448→            CriteriaQuery<League> cq = cb.createQuery(League.class);\n   449→            if (cq != null) {\n   450→                Root<League> league = cq.from(League.class);\n   451→                // EntityType<League> League_ = league.getModel();\n   452→                Join<League, Team> team = league.join(League_.teams);\n   453→                // EntityType<Team> Team_ = team.getModel();\n   454→                Join<Team, Player> player = team.join(Team_.players);\n   455→\n   456→                cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.id), playerId));\n   457→                cq.select(league).distinct(true);\n   458→                TypedQuery<League> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   459→                leagues = q.getResultList();\n   460→            }\n   461→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   462→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   463→        }\n   464→\n   465→        if (leagues == null) {\n   466→            logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"No leagues found for player with ID {0}.\", playerId);\n   467→            return null;\n   468→        } else {\n   469→            Iterator<League> i = leagues.iterator();\n   470→            while (i.hasNext()) {\n   471→                League league = (League) i.next();\n   472→                LeagueDetails leagueDetails = new LeagueDetails(league.getId(),\n   473→                        league.getName(),\n   474→                        league.getSport());\n   475→                detailsList.add(leagueDetails);\n   476→            }\n   477→\n   478→        }\n   479→        return detailsList;\n   480→    }\n   481→\n   482→    @Override\n   483→    public List<String> getSportsOfPlayer(String playerId) {\n   484→        logger.info(\"getSportsOfPlayer\");\n   485→        List<String> sports = new ArrayList<>();\n   486→\n   487→        try {\n   488→            CriteriaQuery<String> cq = cb.createQuery(String.class);\n   489→            if (cq != null) {\n   490→                Root<Player> player = cq.from(Player.class);\n   491→                Join<Player, Team> team = player.join(Player_.teams);\n   492→                Join<Team, League> league = team.join(Team_.league);\n   493→\n   494→                // Get MetaModel from Root\n   495→                // EntityType<Player> Player_ = player.getModel();\n   496→\n   497→                // set the where clause\n   498→                cq.where(cb.equal(player.get(Player_.id), playerId));\n   499→                cq.select(league.get(League_.sport)).distinct(true);\n   500→                TypedQuery<String> q = em.createQuery(cq);\n   501→                sports = q.getResultList();\n   502→            }\n   503→\n   504→            // Player player = em.find(Player.class, playerId);\n   505→            // Iterator<Team> i = player.getTeams().iterator();\n   506→            // while (i.hasNext()) {\n   507→            // Team team = i.next();\n   508→            // League league = team.getLeague();\n   509→            // sports.add(league.getSport());\n   510→            // }\n   511→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   512→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   513→        }\n   514→        return sports;\n   515→    }\n   516→\n   517→    @Override\n   518→    public void createTeamInLeague(TeamDetails teamDetails, String leagueId) {\n   519→        logger.info(\"createTeamInLeague\");\n   520→        try {\n   521→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   522→            if (league == null) {\n   523→                throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"League not found: \" + leagueId);\n   524→            }\n   525→            Team team = new Team(teamDetails.getId(),\n   526→                    teamDetails.getName(),\n   527→                    teamDetails.getCity());\n   528→            em.persist(team);\n   529→            team.setLeague(league);\n   530→            league.addTeam(team);\n   531→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   532→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   533→        }\n   534→    }\n   535→\n   536→    @Override\n   537→    public void removeTeam(String teamId) {\n   538→        logger.info(\"removeTeam\");\n   539→        try {\n   540→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   541→\n   542→            Collection<Player> players = team.getPlayers();\n   543→            Iterator<Player> i = players.iterator();\n   544→            while (i.hasNext()) {\n   545→                Player player = (Player) i.next();\n   546→                player.dropTeam(team);\n   547→            }\n   548→\n   549→            em.remove(team);\n   550→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   551→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   552→        }\n   553→    }\n   554→\n   555→    @Override\n   556→    public TeamDetails getTeam(String teamId) {\n   557→        logger.info(\"getTeam\");\n   558→        TeamDetails teamDetails = null;\n   559→\n   560→        try {\n   561→            Team team = em.find(Team.class, teamId);\n   562→            teamDetails = new TeamDetails(team.getId(), team.getName(), team.getCity());\n   563→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   564→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   565→        }\n   566→        return teamDetails;\n   567→    }\n   568→\n   569→    @Override\n   570→    public void createLeague(LeagueDetails leagueDetails) {\n   571→        logger.info(\"createLeague\");\n   572→        try {\n   573→            if (leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"soccer\")\n   574→                    || leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"swimming\")\n   575→                    || leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"basketball\")\n   576→                    || leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"baseball\")) {\n   577→                SummerLeague league = new SummerLeague(leagueDetails.getId(),\n   578→                        leagueDetails.getName(),\n   579→                        leagueDetails.getSport());\n   580→                em.persist(league);\n   581→            } else if (leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"hockey\")\n   582→                    || leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"skiing\")\n   583→                    || leagueDetails.getSport().equalsIgnoreCase(\"snowboarding\")) {\n   584→                WinterLeague league = new WinterLeague(leagueDetails.getId(),\n   585→                        leagueDetails.getName(),\n   586→                        leagueDetails.getSport());\n   587→                em.persist(league);\n   588→            } else {\n   589→                throw new IncorrectSportException(\"The specified sport is not valid.\");\n   590→            }\n   591→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   592→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   593→        }\n   594→    }\n   595→\n   596→    @Override\n   597→    public void removeLeague(String leagueId) {\n   598→        logger.info(\"removeLeague\");\n   599→        try {\n   600→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   601→            em.remove(league);\n   602→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   603→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   604→        }\n   605→    }\n   606→\n   607→    @Override\n   608→    public LeagueDetails getLeague(String leagueId) {\n   609→        logger.info(\"getLeague\");\n   610→        LeagueDetails leagueDetails = null;\n   611→\n   612→        try {\n   613→            League league = em.find(League.class, leagueId);\n   614→            if (league == null) {\n   615→                return null;\n   616→            }\n   617→            leagueDetails = new LeagueDetails(league.getId(),\n   618→                    league.getName(),\n   619→                    league.getSport());\n   620→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n   621→            throw new EJBException(ex);\n   622→        }\n   623→        return leagueDetails;\n   624→    }\n   625→\n   626→    private List<PlayerDetails> copyPlayersToDetails(List<Player> players) {\n   627→        List<PlayerDetails> detailsList = new ArrayList<>();\n   628→        Iterator<Player> i = players.iterator();\n   629→        while (i.hasNext()) {\n   630→            Player player = (Player) i.next();\n   631→            PlayerDetails playerDetails = new PlayerDetails(player.getId(),\n   632→                    player.getName(),\n   633→                    player.getPosition(),\n   634→                    player.getSalary());\n   635→            detailsList.add(playerDetails);\n   636→        }\n   637→        return detailsList;\n   638→    }\n   639→}\n   640→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"8778044e-d94d-47f3-bde7-c9ac2687c220"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0162nBrQpCMpiLe1Wftk5dH2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakarta.tutorial.roster.request;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     7→import jakarta.ejb.Singleton;\n     8→import jakarta.ejb.Startup;\n     9→import jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttribute;\n    10→import jakarta.ejb.TransactionAttributeType;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    13→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.League;\n    14→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.SummerLeague;\n    15→import jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity.WinterLeague;\n    16→\n    17→@Singleton\n    18→@Startup\n    19→public class DataInitializer {\n    20→\n    21→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(\"roster.request.DataInitializer\");\n    22→\n    23→    @PersistenceContext\n    24→    private EntityManager em;\n    25→\n    26→    @PostConstruct\n    27→    @TransactionAttribute(TransactionAttributeType.REQUIRED)\n    28→    public void init() {\n    29→        seedCanonicalLeagues();\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    private void seedCanonicalLeagues() {\n    33→        try {\n    34→            if (em.find(League.class, \"L1\") == null) {\n    35→                em.persist(new SummerLeague(\"L1\", \"Mountain\", \"Soccer\"));\n    36→            }\n    37→            if (em.find(League.class, \"L2\") == null) {\n    38→                em.persist(new SummerLeague(\"L2\", \"Valley\", \"Basketball\"));\n    39→            }\n    40→            if (em.find(League.class, \"L3\") == null) {\n    41→                em.persist(new SummerLeague(\"L3\", \"Foothills\", \"Soccer\"));\n    42→            }\n    43→            if (em.find(League.class, \"L4\") == null) {\n    44→                em.persist(new WinterLeague(\"L4\", \"Alpine\", \"Snowboarding\"));\n    45→            }\n    46→            logger.info(\"Canonical leagues seeded successfully\");\n    47→        } catch (Exception ex) {\n    48→            logger.log(Level.WARNING, \"Failed to seed canonical leagues\", ex);\n    49→        }\n    50→    }\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"b910132e-9f4f-443d-80b0-fab0269a5260"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016X6PMqtmQQoZZYTUTqhxUN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package jakartaee.tutorial.roster.web;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.List;\n     4→import java.util.logging.Level;\n     5→import java.util.logging.Logger;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     8→import jakarta.ejb.EJBException;\n     9→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.request.Request;\n    10→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.IncorrectSportException;\n    11→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.LeagueDetails;\n    12→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.PlayerDetails;\n    13→import jakarta.tutorial.roster.util.TeamDetails;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.DELETE;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    19→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    20→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    21→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    22→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    23→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Response;\n    24→\n    25→@Path(\"/\")\n    26→@Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    27→public class RosterResource {\n    28→\n    29→    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(\"roster.web.RosterResource\");\n    30→\n    31→    @EJB\n    32→    private Request requestBean;\n    33→\n    34→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n    35→    // League endpoints\n    36→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n    37→\n    38→    @POST\n    39→    @Path(\"/league\")\n    40→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    41→    public Response createLeague(LeagueDetails league) {\n    42→        try {\n    43→            requestBean.createLeague(league);\n    44→            return Response.ok().build();\n    45→        } catch (EJBException e) {\n    46→            if (hasIncorrectSportCause(e)) {\n    47→                return Response.status(Response.Status.BAD_REQUEST)\n    48→                        .entity(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Invalid sport: \" + league.getSport() + \"\\\"}\")\n    49→                        .build();\n    50→            }\n    51→            throw e;\n    52→        }\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    @GET\n    56→    @Path(\"/league/{id}\")\n    57→    public Response getLeague(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n    58→        LeagueDetails league = requestBean.getLeague(id);\n    59→        if (league == null) {\n    60→            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    61→        }\n    62→        return Response.ok(league).build();\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    @DELETE\n    66→    @Path(\"/league/{id}\")\n    67→    public Response removeLeague(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n    68→        requestBean.removeLeague(id);\n    69→        return Response.ok().build();\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    @GET\n    73→    @Path(\"/league/{id}/teams\")\n    74→    public List<TeamDetails> getTeamsOfLeague(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n    75→        return requestBean.getTeamsOfLeague(id);\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n    79→    // Team endpoints\n    80→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n    81→\n    82→    @POST\n    83→    @Path(\"/team/league/{leagueId}\")\n    84→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    85→    public Response createTeamInLeague(TeamDetails team, @PathParam(\"leagueId\") String leagueId) {\n    86→        requestBean.createTeamInLeague(team, leagueId);\n    87→        return Response.ok().build();\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    @GET\n    91→    @Path(\"/team/{id}\")\n    92→    public Response getTeam(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n    93→        TeamDetails team = requestBean.getTeam(id);\n    94→        if (team == null) {\n    95→            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n    96→        }\n    97→        return Response.ok(team).build();\n    98→    }\n    99→\n   100→    @DELETE\n   101→    @Path(\"/team/{id}\")\n   102→    public Response removeTeam(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   103→        requestBean.removeTeam(id);\n   104→        return Response.ok().build();\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    @GET\n   108→    @Path(\"/team/{id}/players\")\n   109→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersOfTeam(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   110→        return requestBean.getPlayersOfTeam(id);\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   114→    // Player endpoints\n   115→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   116→\n   117→    @POST\n   118→    @Path(\"/player\")\n   119→    public Response createPlayer(\n   120→            @QueryParam(\"id\") String id,\n   121→            @QueryParam(\"name\") String name,\n   122→            @QueryParam(\"position\") String position,\n   123→            @QueryParam(\"salary\") double salary) {\n   124→        requestBean.createPlayer(id, name, position, salary);\n   125→        return Response.ok().build();\n   126→    }\n   127→\n   128→    @GET\n   129→    @Path(\"/player/{id}\")\n   130→    public Response getPlayer(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   131→        try {\n   132→            PlayerDetails player = requestBean.getPlayer(id);\n   133→            if (player == null) {\n   134→                return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   135→            }\n   136→            return Response.ok(player).build();\n   137→        } catch (EJBException e) {\n   138→            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   139→        }\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    @DELETE\n   143→    @Path(\"/player/{id}\")\n   144→    public Response removePlayer(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   145→        try {\n   146→            requestBean.removePlayer(id);\n   147→            return Response.ok().build();\n   148→        } catch (EJBException e) {\n   149→            return Response.status(Response.Status.NOT_FOUND).build();\n   150→        }\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    @POST\n   154→    @Path(\"/player/{pid}/team/{tid}\")\n   155→    public Response addPlayerToTeam(@PathParam(\"pid\") String pid, @PathParam(\"tid\") String tid) {\n   156→        requestBean.addPlayer(pid, tid);\n   157→        return Response.ok().build();\n   158→    }\n   159→\n   160→    @DELETE\n   161→    @Path(\"/player/{pid}/team/{tid}\")\n   162→    public Response dropPlayerFromTeam(@PathParam(\"pid\") String pid, @PathParam(\"tid\") String tid) {\n   163→        requestBean.dropPlayer(pid, tid);\n   164→        return Response.ok().build();\n   165→    }\n   166→\n   167→    @GET\n   168→    @Path(\"/player/{id}/leagues\")\n   169→    public List<LeagueDetails> getLeaguesOfPlayer(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   170→        return requestBean.getLeaguesOfPlayer(id);\n   171→    }\n   172→\n   173→    @GET\n   174→    @Path(\"/player/{id}/sports\")\n   175→    public List<String> getSportsOfPlayer(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   176→        return requestBean.getSportsOfPlayer(id);\n   177→    }\n   178→\n   179→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   180→    // Query endpoints\n   181→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   182→\n   183→    @GET\n   184→    @Path(\"/players\")\n   185→    public List<PlayerDetails> getAllPlayers() {\n   186→        return requestBean.getAllPlayers();\n   187→    }\n   188→\n   189→    @GET\n   190→    @Path(\"/players/position/{position}\")\n   191→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByPosition(@PathParam(\"position\") String position) {\n   192→        return requestBean.getPlayersByPosition(position);\n   193→    }\n   194→\n   195→    @GET\n   196→    @Path(\"/players/salary/higher/{name}\")\n   197→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByHigherSalary(@PathParam(\"name\") String name) {\n   198→        return requestBean.getPlayersByHigherSalary(name);\n   199→    }\n   200→\n   201→    @GET\n   202→    @Path(\"/players/salary/range\")\n   203→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySalaryRange(\n   204→            @QueryParam(\"low\") double low,\n   205→            @QueryParam(\"high\") double high) {\n   206→        return requestBean.getPlayersBySalaryRange(low, high);\n   207→    }\n   208→\n   209→    @GET\n   210→    @Path(\"/players/league/{id}\")\n   211→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByLeague(@PathParam(\"id\") String id) {\n   212→        return requestBean.getPlayersByLeagueId(id);\n   213→    }\n   214→\n   215→    @GET\n   216→    @Path(\"/players/sport/{sport}\")\n   217→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersBySport(@PathParam(\"sport\") String sport) {\n   218→        return requestBean.getPlayersBySport(sport);\n   219→    }\n   220→\n   221→    @GET\n   222→    @Path(\"/players/city/{city}\")\n   223→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersByCity(@PathParam(\"city\") String city) {\n   224→        return requestBean.getPlayersByCity(city);\n   225→    }\n   226→\n   227→    @GET\n   228→    @Path(\"/players/not-on-team\")\n   229→    public List<PlayerDetails> getPlayersNotOnTeam() {\n   230→        return requestBean.getPlayersNotOnTeam();\n   231→    }\n   232→\n   233→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   234→    // Helpers\n   235→    // -----------------------------------------------------------------------\n   236→\n   237→    private boolean hasIncorrectSportCause(EJBException e) {\n   238→        Throwable cause = e.getCause();\n   239→        while (cause != null) {\n   240→            if (cause instanceof IncorrectSportException) {\n   241→                return true;\n   242→            }\n   243→            cause = cause.getCause();\n   244→        }\n   245→        return false;\n   246→    }\n   247→}\n   248→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"89f5542a-665a-4fea-969a-e66ac88f86a2"}
