{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MuLoShbAYq9Bx3qNMK4Cyj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     2→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→  \n     6→  <parent>\n     7→    <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n     8→    <artifactId>roster</artifactId>\n     9→    <version>1.0.0</version>\n    10→  </parent>\n    11→  \n    12→  <artifactId>roster-ear</artifactId>\n    13→  <packaging>ear</packaging>\n    14→\n    15→  <properties>\n    16→    <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>\n    17→    <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>\n    18→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    19→  </properties>\n    20→  <name>roster-ear</name>\n    21→\n    22→  <dependencies>\n    23→    <!-- Pull in the modules we want packaged into the EAR -->\n    24→    <dependency>\n    25→      <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    26→      <artifactId>roster-common</artifactId>\n    27→      <version>${project.version}</version>\n    28→    </dependency>\n    29→    <dependency>\n    30→      <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    31→      <artifactId>roster-ejb</artifactId>\n    32→      <version>${project.version}</version>\n    33→      <type>ejb</type>\n    34→    </dependency>\n    35→    <dependency>\n    36→      <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    37→      <artifactId>roster-appclient</artifactId>\n    38→      <version>${project.version}</version>\n    39→    </dependency>\n    40→    <dependency>\n    41→      <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    42→      <artifactId>roster-web</artifactId>\n    43→      <version>${project.version}</version>\n    44→      <type>war</type>\n    45→    </dependency>\n    46→    <dependency>\n    47→      <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    48→      <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    49→      <version>2.3.232</version>\n    50→    </dependency>\n    51→  </dependencies>\n    52→\n    53→  <build>\n    54→    <plugins>\n    55→      <plugin>\n    56→        <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    57→        <artifactId>maven-ear-plugin</artifactId>\n    58→        <version>3.3.0</version>\n    59→        <configuration>\n    60→          <generateApplicationXml>true</generateApplicationXml>\n    61→          <defaultLibBundleDir>lib</defaultLibBundleDir>\n    62→          <modules>\n    63→            <ejbModule>\n    64→              <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    65→              <artifactId>roster-ejb</artifactId>\n    66→            </ejbModule>\n    67→            <jarModule>\n    68→              <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    69→              <artifactId>roster-appclient</artifactId>\n    70→            </jarModule>\n    71→            <webModule>\n    72→              <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    73→              <artifactId>roster-web</artifactId>\n    74→              <contextRoot>/roster</contextRoot>\n    75→            </webModule>\n    76→          </modules>\n    77→        </configuration>\n    78→      </plugin>\n    79→      <plugin>\n    80→        <groupId>io.openliberty.tools</groupId>\n    81→        <artifactId>liberty-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    82→        <configuration>\n    83→          <copyDependencies>\n    84→            <dependencyGroup>\n    85→              <location>${project.build.directory}/liberty/wlp/usr/shared/resources</location>\n    86→              <dependency>\n    87→                <groupId>com.h2database</groupId>\n    88→                <artifactId>h2</artifactId>\n    89→              </dependency>\n    90→            </dependencyGroup>\n    91→          </copyDependencies>\n    92→        </configuration>\n    93→      </plugin>\n    94→    </plugins>\n    95→  </build>\n    96→</project>\n    97→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"3888888a-a1cf-4d3c-9eed-e0b6723bac94"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01BmDyM3updUi2hRXbPMoVwZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me update the todo and start the migration. The key changes needed:\n\n1. **Multi-module EAR** → **Single Quarkus module**\n2. **EJB (@Stateful, @Singleton, @Startup)** → **CDI beans (@ApplicationScoped, @Transactional)**\n3. **@EJB injection** → **@Inject**\n4. **EJBException** → **RuntimeException**\n5. **@Remote interface** → **Regular interface**\n6. **JPA static metamodel** → **Hibernate JPA Modelgen**\n7. **JSF beans** → **Drop (REST-only in Quarkus)**\n8. **Open Liberty server.xml** → **application.properties**\n9. **H2 in-memory** → **H2 with Quarkus Agroal**\n10. **Liberty:run** → **Quarkus uber-jar**"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":14797,"cache_read_input_tokens":46557,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":14797,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":636},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d48893e1-9e26-43a0-bfcb-cd1badbcc494","uuid":"42095df0-2c80-4fac-aa3f-6fb7f364af1f"}
